<paragraph blockId="15.[144,759,1514,1903]" pageId="15" pageNumber="87">
Medium size species (
<quantity box="[431,530,1544,1566]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1199999999999999" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" unit="mm" value="11.2">11.2 mm</quantity>
) with moderately broad abdomen; similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray, 2012" authorityName="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray" authorityYear="2012" box="[467,611,1575,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="personata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[467,611,1575,1596]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="87">Q. personata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[618,705,1575,1596]" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but with higher density of body hairs, which are extensively golden yellow in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1946" box="[407,507,1636,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cestus">
<emphasis box="[407,507,1636,1658]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="87">Q. cestus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but whitish in 
<taxonomicName authority="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray, 2012" authorityName="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="personata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="87">Q. personata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[226,313,1667,1688]" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1946" box="[367,467,1667,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cestus">
<emphasis box="[367,467,1667,1688]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="87">Q. cestus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bf is 1.5, the pro- and mesotibia have brown markings, and the scutellum is wholly pale haired, whereas in 
<taxonomicName authority="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray, 2012" authorityName="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray" authorityYear="2012" box="[524,668,1728,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="personata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[524,668,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="87">Q. personata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[675,759,1728,1749]" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
bf is 2 (
<figureCitation box="[229,310,1758,1780]" captionStart="Figures 51–55" captionStartId="30.[164,254,781,800]" captionTargetBox="[389,1218,199,748]" captionTargetId="figure-373@30.[387,1219,195,751]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="Figures 51–55. Quichuana right antennae, lateral inner view: 51, Quichuana seiferti sp. nov., male paratype; 52, Quichuana zoricae sp. nov., female paratype; 53, Quichuana melas, male holotype; 54, Quichuana personata sp. nov., female holotype; 55, Quichuana pogonosa sp. nov., male from type locality. Scale bars: 1 mm (lower bar applies to Fig. 55 only)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5408567" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5408567/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="87">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
), the pro- and mesotibia are black, and the scutellum has a few black hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[144,759,1514,1903]" lastBlockId="15.[806,1422,198,342]" pageId="15" pageNumber="87">
<materialsCitation country="Venezuela" elevation="2880" location="Duida" municipality="Although" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Amazonas">
<collectingMunicipality box="[168,274,1820,1842]" pageId="15" pageNumber="87">Although</collectingMunicipality>
these two similar species are found in 
<collectingCountry box="[144,263,1850,1872]" name="Venezuela" pageId="15" pageNumber="87">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[341,390,1851,1872]" pageId="15" pageNumber="87">type</typeStatus>
localities are very different. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:710797611067FFC0ABB178999F5D1FDA:FC7170AC1067FFC0ABD77E4D9ABC197D" box="[144,214,1881,1903]" country="Venezuela" municipality="Although" name="Duida" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" stateProvince="Amazonas">Duida</location>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1946" box="[239,339,1881,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cestus">
<emphasis box="[239,339,1881,1902]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="87">Q. cestus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) is a mountain in the southern state of 
<collectingRegion box="[919,1039,198,219]" country="Venezuela" name="Amazonas" pageId="15" pageNumber="87">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
, with the highest altitude at 
<elevation box="[806,951,228,250]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.88" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" unit="m" value="2880.0">
<quantity box="[806,890,229,250]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.88" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" unit="m" value="2880.0">2880 m</quantity>
a.s.l.
</elevation>
</materialsCitation>
, 
<materialsCitation country="Venezuela" county="San Antonio" elevation="1400" location="Duida" municipality="Altos" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Amazonas">
very rainy, and with unique vegetation. 
<collectingCounty box="[806,947,259,281]" pageId="15" pageNumber="87">San Antonio</collectingCounty>
de los 
<collectingMunicipality box="[1025,1084,259,281]" pageId="15" pageNumber="87">Altos</collectingMunicipality>
(
<taxonomicName authority="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray, 2012" authorityName="Ricarte &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Rotheray" authorityYear="2012" box="[1100,1243,259,281]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Quichuana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="personata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1100,1243,259,281]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="87">Q. personata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1250,1338,259,280]" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), about 
<quantity box="[806,890,290,312]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" unit="km" value="800.0">800 km</quantity>
to the north of 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:710797611067FFC0ABB178999F5D1FDA:FC7170AC1067FFC0AF7178369E141F2A" box="[1078,1150,290,312]" country="Venezuela" county="San Antonio" municipality="Altos" name="Duida" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" stateProvince="Amazonas">Duida</location>
, is close to the sea and sits at 
<elevation box="[889,1033,320,342]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" unit="m" value="1400.0">
<quantity box="[889,973,320,342]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="15" pageNumber="87" unit="m" value="1400.0">1400 m</quantity>
a.s.l.
</elevation>
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
